Preheat the #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Spread the @McCain Home Chips{400%grams} on a #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Bake on the top shelf, ~{25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @burger buns{2}. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%grams}.

Halve, peel and slice the @red onion{1} as thinly as you can.

Pop half into a #small bowl{} and add the @sugar{1%tsp} and half the @cider vinegar{30%ml}. Add a pinch of salt, mix together and set aside to pickle.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @olive oil{1%tbsp} with the remaining cider vinegar. Add a pinch of sugar, season with salt and pepper, then add the tomatoes and mix together. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @lamb mince{200%grams} and the remaining onion. Fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a spoon to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

While it fries, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the lamb is cooked, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with salt and pepper.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir in the @tomato puree{30%grams}, @korma curry paste{50%grams} and garlic. Fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir through the @chicken stock paste{10%grams}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml}. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the sauce has thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

While the lamb simmers, pop the burger buns into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the lamb is ready, stir in the @peas{120%grams} and cook until piping hot, ~{1%minute}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Remove from the heat.

Share the burger bun between your plates, spreading the @butter{20%grams} onto the cut sides.

Spoon the beef keema onto the bun halves and top with the pickled onion.

Toss the @baby leaf mix{20%grams} through the tomatoes. Serve the tomato salad and chips on the side.

Enjoy!